{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set book = card_data.book %}
{% set gate = card_data.information_gate %}
{% set display_managers = card_data.managers | sort(attribute="capital_weight", reverse=true) %}
{% set tier_labels = {
  "R": "Returns only",
  "E": "Exposure summaries",
  "P": "Positions and trades"
} %}
{% set source_labels = {
  "returns_regression_proxy": "Returns regression estimate",
  "coarsened_exposure_emission": "Exposure summary",
  "position_transparent_emission": "Position-derived exposure"
} %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/p2.css">
{% endblock %}

{% macro signed(x) %}{{ "%+.3f"|format(x) }}{% endmacro %}
{% macro pct(x) %}{{ "%.1f"|format(x * 100) }}%{% endmacro %}
{% macro whole_pct(x) %}{{ "%.0f"|format(x * 100) }}%{% endmacro %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="p2-current" data-current-output="reconciliation" aria-labelledby="p2-current-title">
  <header class="p2-current__header">
    <p class="p2-current__kicker">Current output: reconciliation only</p>
    <h2 id="p2-current-title">Compare each manager on the evidence it actually provides</h2>
    <p>
      The three evidence types do not yet have calibrated, comparable error rates. The
      honest current view therefore keeps every manager interval separate and withholds
      a single fused book estimate.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="p2-tier-key" aria-label="Evidence types">
    {% for tier in ["R", "E", "P"] %}
    <span class="tier-badge">{{ tier_labels[tier] }}</span>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div class="p2-manager-rows">
    {% for manager in display_managers %}
    <article class="p2-manager-row">
      <header>
        <div>
          <strong>{{ manager.name }}</strong>
          <span>{{ pct(manager.capital_weight) }} of book capital</span>
        </div>
        <span class="tier-badge">{{ tier_labels[manager.tier] }}</span>
      </header>
      <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="manager-beta"
           data-lo="{{ manager.posterior.ci_lo }}"
           data-point="{{ manager.posterior.point }}"
           data-hi="{{ manager.posterior.ci_hi }}"
           aria-label="{{ manager.name }} provisional interval {{ signed(manager.posterior.ci_lo) }} to {{ signed(manager.posterior.ci_hi) }}">
        <span class="interval-stat__label">Provisional manager market-beta interval</span>
        <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ signed(manager.posterior.point) }}</span>
        <div class="interval-stat__rail">
          <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
          <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
        </div>
        <span class="interval-stat__range">
          {{ whole_pct(manager.posterior.level) }} interval
          {{ signed(manager.posterior.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ signed(manager.posterior.ci_hi) }}
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="p2-manager-row__source">
        Evidence source: {{ source_labels[manager.observation_source] }}
      </p>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<aside class="p2-explainer" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2>What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <h3>What you are looking at</h3>
  <p>
    Fifteen manager-level estimates, each labelled by capital weight, evidence source,
    and uncertainty. They are intentionally not collapsed into one number.
  </p>
  <h3>How to read it</h3>
  <p>
    Compare interval width before comparing point estimates. Returns-only estimates are
    least direct; disclosed exposure summaries are more informative; position-derived
    exposures are most direct. Those qualitative differences do not yet license one
    common precision scale.
  </p>
  <p><a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/p2.html">Read the full article</a>.</p>
</aside>

<details class="p2-teaching-scenario">
  <summary>Provisional teaching calculation — not an operational result</summary>
  <div class="p2-teaching-scenario__body">
    <p>
      This synthetic scenario assumes provisional measurement errors to demonstrate how
      a future calibrated fusion could work. The assumptions are the lesson; the fused
      number is not a current allocator output.
    </p>
    <div class="interval-stat p2-book" data-domain="book-beta"
         data-lo="{{ book.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ book.point }}" data-hi="{{ book.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">Fused book net market beta</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ signed(book.point) }}</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail">
        <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
        <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
      </div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">
        {{ whole_pct(card_data.constants.credible_level) }} credible interval
        {{ signed(book.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ signed(book.ci_hi) }}
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="p2-gain-grid">
      {% for state in card_data.counterfactuals %}
      <article class="p2-counterfactual interval-stat" data-domain="book-beta"
               data-lo="{{ state.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ state.point }}"
               data-hi="{{ state.ci_hi }}">
        <span class="interval-stat__label">{{ state.label | replace("All R tier", "All managers measured from returns") | replace("Every sleeve at least E", "Every manager has an exposure summary") }}</span>
        <span class="interval-stat__value">sd {{ "%.4f"|format(state.sd) }}</span>
        <div class="interval-stat__rail">
          <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
          <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
        </div>
        <span class="interval-stat__range">
          {{ whole_pct(state.level) }} interval {{ signed(state.ci_lo) }} &hellip;
          {{ signed(state.ci_hi) }}
        </span>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <p>
      Under these provisional assumptions, the richer-evidence scenario narrows the
      standard deviation by {{ pct(gate.gain) }}, above the illustrative {{ pct(gate.floor) }}
      threshold. That arithmetic demonstrates the method but does not calibrate the
      evidence types.
    </p>
  </div>
</details>

<section class="p2-boundary">
  <h2>What remains unresolved</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>The book variance omits covariance cross-terms by design;</strong> overlap and
    crowding require a separate method. Time-varying evidence quality and live error
    calibration are also unresolved. This exhibit measures exposure; it does not
    allocate capital or recommend a trade.
  </p>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>
  A future fused view would update each manager's exposure estimate against the same
  weak prior using an evidence-specific error scale, then aggregate the manager
  posteriors by capital weight. Until those error scales are calibrated on comparable
  evidence, the public result remains the manager-by-manager reconciliation above.
</p>
{% endblock %}
